## 1. Definitions

- **"AEGIS"** refers to the AEGIS Post-Quantum Cryptography Library, including all source code, documentation, and related materials.
- **"Licensee"** refers to any individual or entity that receives, uses, or distributes AEGIS.
- **"External Implementations"** refers specifically to the pqrust, pqclean, and pqnist components, which were created by third parties.
- **"Proprietary Components"** refers to all AEGIS components except the External Implementations, including but not limited to pqpython, pqnodejs, pqwasm, pqwasi, pqvm, pqnostd, pqhw, pqmobile, pqwear, pqmavr, and all core AEGIS framework files.

